  "texts": [
    "To address these risks, regulatory bodies are beginning to develop consumer protection regulations for blockchain technology.",
    "For example, the European Union's GDPR applies to blockchain technology and provides individuals with the right to have their personal data erased from the blockchain (Eichler et al. 2018).",
    "In the United States, the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) has taken action against companies that conducted initial coin offerings (ICOs) without registering them as securities, which is required by law (DuPont 2019).",
    "In addition to Ponzi schemes, hacking attacks, and data breaches, there are other types of illegal activities that may occur on the blockchain.",
    "One example is the use of blockchain for money laundering and terrorist financing."
  ],
